wikipedia_page.main: Doris 'Dolly' Gubbins (married name Doris Evans) was a Welsh international table tennis player.

link_mentions.page: List of World Table Tennis Championships medalists
1926 World Table Tennis Championships – Women's Singles
response: Mária Mednyánszky defeated Doris Gubbins in the final of this event 21–15, 21–19.
She won a silver medal at the 1928 World Table Tennis Championships in the women's doubles with Doris Gubbins. She also won an English Open title.

link_mentions.page: 1928 World Table Tennis Championships – Women's Doubles
response: Fanchette Flamm and Mária Mednyánszky defeated Doris Gubbins and Brenda Sommerville in the final by three sets to nil.
